{"id":"f4ec4cb6-3fd8-4c0c-8a1c-7687b0df413e","title":"1498/04/07","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"185671c1-cbb7-43f7-ba47-ebcf8c70d4d7","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"7th April. There was arranged in the Piazza de\u0027 Signori a scaffold 50 braccia long, and 10 braccia wide, and 4 braccia high; and its foundation was of certain wooden beams, on the four sides of which was made a wall of unbaked bricks, half a braccio high, with gravel and rubbish in the middle, and everything covered, in fact, so that the fire could not touch the beams underneath; all along the edges of the said platform were laid big logs of wood, to the height of 2\u00A0\u00BD braccia, the length being 40 braccia on each side, 4 braccia being left at each end; whilst in the middle a space was left of 2 braccia in width, along which the Frati would have to pass. Outside and inside of these logs of wood was piled a quantity of brushwood and boughs, so that the passage remaining was only one braccio in width; and, besides this, all the wood was soaked with oil, spirit and resin, to make it burn better. The date having been fixed, the Frati of San Marco and of San Francesco, who were to pass through the fire, as they had agreed and signed to do, were to present themselves at 17 in the afternoon of the said day (1 p.m.); it having been resolved that Fra Domenico of Pescia should enter for those of San Marco, and Fra Giuliano de\u0027 Rondinegli of the Osservanza for the Franciscans. At the time fixed, the Franciscans arrived, and went into the Loggia de\u0027 Signori, which had been divided by a boarding in the middle, and they stood silently at the end towards San Piero Scheraggio. Then came the Dominicans, with much pomp, a number of Frati, about 250, walking two and two, followed by Fra Domenico carrying a crucifix, and then Fra Girolamo carrying the Host; whilst behind them was an immense crowd with torches and tapers, devoutly singing psalms. Having entered the Loggia and prepared an altar, they sang a mass; and the people awaited the great spectacle. After a wait of several hours, everybody began to wonder.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"484961b5-b6f4-4cb4-9fae-0e49a19f4224","type":"codex/time-reference","start":0,"end":8,"value":"750c369d-11da-47d4-9618-29b2ab6da2e7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"365173c4-a45e-43fb-8d00-9fe5005a7708","type":"tei/core/date","start":0,"end":8,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["when|1498-04-07"]},{"id":"d3e0c62c-9660-4dfc-b01c-f144334e22f8","type":"page","start":0,"end":1921,"value":"135","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"4ab25519-7e47-4f5c-a84a-166100ff1035","type":"style/superscript","start":1,"end":2,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c82e1fcd-b14e-42d7-8952-12ea1bfce6bf","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":37,"end":54,"value":"dd1982d9-b1a5-4429-af68-92d184193bbf","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"2e7bb2d8-7736-4fc7-ba65-a4047e11e615","type":"style/italics","start":37,"end":54,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"e10c6f7d-b07b-445e-b026-ad4550dcb18e","type":"language","start":37,"end":54,"value":"it","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"2c4281c3-e6ac-45bf-8c84-269cb4262812","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":58,"end":65,"value":"84f8eb2f-18fd-4b71-b041-52248ae67d31","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"72ddb831-dc58-489d-830a-5857f274bf49","type":"style/italics","start":70,"end":76,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"e6e1d472-01e3-4887-8590-f2df08000559","type":"codex/document-reference","start":77,"end":77,"value":"f4e1790e-16dd-4101-91f4-ef0ce200e82f","zeroPoint":true,"metadata":[]},{"id":"a83765d2-43d9-4b9b-8bab-304d48467ddf","type":"style/italics","start":91,"end":97,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7e9cfcc0-5d1b-40ef-8c92-40cbd20a50df","type":"style/italics","start":111,"end":117,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"5296d79d-c795-454d-83d0-224be6a1dbd6","type":"codex